                <head>No. 507.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Mathews</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-04-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">April</hi> 13, 1880</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 165.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 353, transmitting a copy of the
                    circular of the Moorish minister of foreign affairs relative to the Sultan’s
                    desire that Moorish subjects naturalized in foreign countries shall become
                    amenable to Moorish jurisdiction, has been received, and I take pleasure in
                    informing you that your action thereunder, based upon the treaty of September
                    16, 1836, between the governments of the United States of America and Morocco,
                    meets with entire approval.</p>
                <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. M. EVARTS.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
